        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Background Workers for GenAI"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM calls routinely take 5\u201330 seconds. Serving them synchronously keeps an HTTP connection open for the full duration, exhausts thread pools under load, and gives clients no visibility into progress. Background workers decouple the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "submission",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " of a job from its "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "execution",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "retrieval",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The client gets a job ID immediately, the worker runs the LLM call at its own pace, and the result is fetched or pushed when ready."
          }
        ]
      },
